author: Andrew Mark Miller
title: Compare the Super Bowl Ads During Obama’s Last Year In Office to This Years, and You’ll Notice 1 HUGE Difference…
text:
06:46pm February 5, 2017 Do you like this article? 
The day of the big game is finally here and Americans all across the country are ready to eat, drink, watch football, and skip work tomorrow. 
A lot of people out there are watching the game even though they don’t care about football. 
That’s because there are always some good commercials to check out. 
The country is a lot different than it was in 2016. 
You can see how things have changed just by looking at the 2017 commercials and comparing them to 2016. 
Here are a few examples… 
In 2016, Audi released a commercial about how driving their car is like driving a rocket ship. 
In 2017, their commercial was about a Dad having to explain to his daughter that society doesn’t view her as equal to a man. 
In 2016, Kia’s commercial was about how their cars were cool enough for James Bond. 
In 2017, the commercial was about the environment or something. 
See where I’m going with this? 
I’ve got a pretty good feeling we are going to see some agendas being pushed over the next few hours. 
Let’s also not forget about the halftime lecture we are probably going to get from Lady Gaga. 
Stay tuned…
